				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\tilde{x}}_i$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M80"><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>x</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">~</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_3983_Article_IEq40.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is a solid symbol. Consequently, the previous example <inline-formula id="IEq41"><alternatives><tex-math id="M81">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
